# Core Functions Reference

This document summarizes the core functions/components in the workspace with short descriptions, 
parameters, return values and important side-effects. Click the links to open the implementation.

## Maps
- [`ReportsMap`](components/ReportsMap.tsx) — [components/ReportsMap.tsx](components/ReportsMap.tsx)  
  Renders a Leaflet map with markers for multiple reports.
  - Parameters: `reports: Report[]`, `height?: string`, `basePath?: string`
  - Side-effects: creates custom marker icons (`createCustomIcon`) and logs map load state.
  - Notes: filters reports with numeric `latitude`/`longitude` and computes center from locations.

- [`createCustomIcon`](components/ReportsMap.tsx) — [components/ReportsMap.tsx](components/ReportsMap.tsx)  
  Helper that returns a Leaflet `divIcon` (client-only). Returns `undefined` server-side.

- [`MapDisplay`](components/MapDisplay.tsx) — [components/MapDisplay.tsx](components/MapDisplay.tsx)  
  Single-location map with a popup. Shows loading placeholder until client-side mount.
  - Parameters: `latitude: number`, `longitude: number`, `address?: string`, `height?: string`
  - Behavior: Renders `MapContainer`, `TileLayer`, `Marker`, `Popup`.

- [`MapDisplayWrapper`](components/MapDisplayWrapper.tsx) — [components/MapDisplayWrapper.tsx](components/MapDisplayWrapper.tsx)  
  Client/SSR-safe wrapper around `MapDisplay` to avoid server-side Leaflet issues.

- [`MapLocationPicker`](components/MapLocationPicker.tsx) — [components/MapLocationPicker.tsx](components/MapLocationPicker.tsx)  
  Interactive picker used on report creation. Supports clicking map and current location detection.
  - Parameters: `onLocationSelect`, `initialLocation`, `initialAddress`

- [`MapLocationPickerWrapper`](components/MapLocationPickerWrapper.tsx) — [components/MapLocationPickerWrapper.tsx](components/MapLocationPickerWrapper.tsx)  
  Wrapper that ensures the picker only mounts client-side.

## Toasts & Notifications
- [`useToast`](hooks/use-toast.ts) — [hooks/use-toast.ts](hooks/use-toast.ts)  
  Custom toast hook (inspired by `react-hot-toast`).
  - Returns: `{ toasts, toast, dismiss }`
  - Behavior: stores shared in-memory toasts, registers listeners, exposes `toast` factory and `dismiss`.

- [`toast`](hooks/use-toast.ts) — [hooks/use-toast.ts](hooks/use-toast.ts)  
  Factory to create a toast programmatically. Returns `{ id, dismiss, update }`.
  - Side-effects: dispatches ADD_TOAST, UPDATE_TOAST, DISMISS_TOAST actions and auto-removal handlers.

- [`Toaster`](components/ui/toaster.tsx) — [components/ui/toaster.tsx](components/ui/toaster.tsx)  
  Renders toasts from `useToast` using the UI toast primitives.

- [`Toaster` (Sonner)](components/ui/sonner.tsx) — [components/ui/sonner.tsx](components/ui/sonner.tsx)  
  Sonner-based global toaster component that uses theme context. Alternative to the built-in toast system.

- UI toast primitives in [`components/ui/toast.tsx`](components/ui/toast.tsx) — [components/ui/toast.tsx](components/ui/toast.tsx)  
  Low-level Radix/primitive components (Toast, ToastTitle, ToastDescription, ToastViewport, etc.).

## Authentication & Supabase
- [`supabase`](lib/supabase.ts) — [lib/supabase.ts](lib/supabase.ts)  
  Supabase client instance created from env vars. Exports `Report` and `Student` type definitions.
  - Side-effects: validates env var formats and throws if missing.

- [`signIn`](lib/auth.ts) — [lib/auth.ts](lib/auth.ts)  
  Calls `supabase.auth.signInWithPassword` (or equivalent) to authenticate a user.
  - Parameters: `email: string`, `password: string`
  - Throws on auth error.

- [`signUp`](lib/auth.ts) — [lib/auth.ts](lib/auth.ts)  
  Creates an auth user, uploads optional profile image to storage, inserts student profile row.
  - Parameters: `email`, `password`, `name`, `department?`, `imageFile?`
  - Side-effects: uploads to `report-photos` bucket and creates `students` row.

- [`signOut`](lib/auth.ts) — [lib/auth.ts](lib/auth.ts)  
  Signs the current user out via `supabase.auth.signOut()`.

- [`getCurrentUser`](lib/auth.ts) — [lib/auth.ts](lib/auth.ts)  
  Returns the current Supabase auth user.

- [`getUserProfile`](lib/auth.ts) — [lib/auth.ts](lib/auth.ts)  
  Fetches the `students` table profile for a given user id; returns `maybeSingle()`.

